Presently, com.atlassian.activeobjects.external.ActiveObjects implements much but not all of the functionality of net.java.ao.EntityManager.

Among the missing items are accessors to FieldNameConverter and TableNameConverter instances, such that these are presently accessible only after RawEntity objects have been created or retrieved (permitting an EntityManager instance to be retrieved, and the converter objects to be accessed, through same).

For purposes of building higher-level interfaces on top of ActiveObjects, however, this is inadequate -- there are legitimate reasons to want to build field<->accessor maps before any instances exist (such as using reflection to build a higher-level API, removing the plugin author's need to be aware of field names in acting as an end user to the AO API).

