When creating an App Link between JIRA and FECRU, wheter the Project App Link is created or not, the tabs 'Source' and 'Reviews' are shown on issues and Project details.

According to the [doc|http://confluence.atlassian.com/display/JIRA/Integrating+JIRA+with+FishEye#IntegratingJIRAwithFishEye-Step4LinkFishEyeRepositoriestoJIRAProjects], Project App Link:

{quote}
Associating JIRA projects with FishEye repositories or Crucible projects is recommended as it greatly improves JIRA's responsiveness when your users view the 'Source' or 'Review' tabs on JIRA issues.
{quote}

For my understanding, the Project App Link should be set to map projects and repos.

However, when configuring JIRA with a different tool, e.g. Subversion plugin, even not having info on FECRU side regarding a particular project, once it's placed on the repo configured with the plugin, the tabs are shown. 

Is it possible to make the tabs available only when the Project App Link is created?

